@startmindmap
* ML-DSA\n(a stamp a quantum computer cannot fake)
** The problem
*** Quantum computers can fake today's stamps
*** We need a lock built from a different puzzle
** Hiding the secret
*** Small secret numbers
*** Multiply by a big public grid
*** Add "fuzz" so nobody can divide it back
** Signing (the 3-move game)
*** Random scribble = commitment
*** Blend message + scribble = surprise question
*** Stir secret in = the answer
** Staying inside the lines
*** Toss any answer that leans too far
*** Retry with a fresh scribble (about 4-5 times)
*** Keeps the secret from leaking
** The sticky note (hint)
*** Public key is shrunk to save space
*** Hint tells the checker how to fix the rounding
** Checking
*** Redo the math from the public key
*** Run the same blender on the message
*** Numbers match = real signature
** Three sizes
*** ML-DSA-44 / 65 / 87
*** Bigger = safer but heavier
*** Cost: bigger keys and signatures
@endmindmap
